<graph edgedefault="undirected"><node id="LightRAG">
  <data key="d0">LightRAG</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">LightRAG is a retrieval-augmented generation framework designed for efficient development of RAG applications.&lt;SEP&gt;LightRAG is an advanced framework that improves upon traditional RAG approaches by offering simpler API design, faster retrieval performance, better vector database integration, and optimized prompting strategies.&lt;SEP&gt;LightRAG is a tool that supports vector search operations and includes a built-in nano-vectordb for easy deployments.&lt;SEP&gt;LightRAG is an organization that supports multiple vector databases to enable flexible deployment options for various applications.&lt;SEP&gt;LightRAG is a framework that enables the selective retrieval of relevant content in various deployment options.&lt;SEP&gt;LightRAG is a framework that can be deployed in production through various approaches to enhance retrieval-augmented generation.&lt;SEP&gt;LightRAG is a framework designed to address hallucination problems in retrieval-augmented generation (RAG) systems.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b82a84a0db12fa70b3252294cbb07cfa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3ab88a7ea07b155c41c81dc1fa3ffb65&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a7534773ede26ba695c6f58ad56a167d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c4a9c90e59381a08a8f6133a6bedd53d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-678dd7910ca01e209fe807783a33d293&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0a6a2a571099c70c7e20dbd90da662e2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-42de391f02d01ca65205e069a3947cfc</data>
  <data key="d4">lightrag/evaluation/sample_documents/01_lightrag_overview.md&lt;SEP&gt;lightrag/evaluation/sample_documents/03_lightrag_improvements.md&lt;SEP&gt;lightrag/evaluation/sample_documents/04_supported_databases.md&lt;SEP&gt;lightrag/evaluation/sample_documents/05_evaluation_and_deployment.md&lt;SEP&gt;lightrag/evaluation/sample_documents/README.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1775461531</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="HKUDS">
  <data key="d0">HKUDS</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">HKUDS, or Hong Kong University Data Science Lab, developed the LightRAG framework.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b82a84a0db12fa70b3252294cbb07cfa</data>
  <data key="d4">lightrag/evaluation/sample_documents/01_lightrag_overview.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1775461429</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Large Language Models">
  <data key="d0">Large Language Models</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Large language models (LLMs) are AI models that generate text but face limitations like hallucinations and knowledge cutoffs.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b82a84a0db12fa70b3252294cbb07cfa</data>
  <data key="d4">lightrag/evaluation/sample_documents/01_lightrag_overview.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1775461429</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Document-Grounded Responses">
  <data key="d0">Document-Grounded Responses</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Document-grounded responses are generated using external documents to ensure the accuracy of outputs from LLMs.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b82a84a0db12fa70b3252294cbb07cfa</data>
  <data key="d4">lightrag/evaluation/sample_documents/01_lightrag_overview.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1775461429</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="External Knowledge Retrieval">
  <data key="d0">External Knowledge Retrieval</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">External knowledge retrieval is a process used in LightRAG to enhance the capabilities of large language models.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b82a84a0db12fa70b3252294cbb07cfa</data>
  <data key="d4">lightrag/evaluation/sample_documents/01_lightrag_overview.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1775461429</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Limitations of Large Language Models">
  <data key="d0">Limitations of Large Language Models</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The limitations of large language models include knowledge cutoffs, hallucinations, and a lack of domain-specific expertise.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b82a84a0db12fa70b3252294cbb07cfa</data>
  <data key="d4">lightrag/evaluation/sample_documents/01_lightrag_overview.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1775461429</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Hallucination Problem">
  <data key="d0">Hallucination Problem</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The hallucination problem refers to the tendency of large language models to generate incorrect or fabricated responses.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b82a84a0db12fa70b3252294cbb07cfa</data>
  <data key="d4">lightrag/evaluation/sample_documents/01_lightrag_overview.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1775461429</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="RAG System">
  <data key="d0">RAG System</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The RAG system is a framework that uses retrieval, embedding, and language model components to generate intelligent responses.&lt;SEP&gt;The RAG system refers to components involved in retrieval-augmented generation processes.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-2a891514222c7fefbcc45259ee3bb8c2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-42de391f02d01ca65205e069a3947cfc</data>
  <data key="d4">lightrag/evaluation/sample_documents/02_rag_architecture.md&lt;SEP&gt;lightrag/evaluation/sample_documents/README.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1775461531</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Retrieval System">
  <data key="d0">Retrieval System</data>
  <data key="d1">component</data>
  <data key="d2">The retrieval system is the first component of the RAG system that finds relevant documents from large collections using vector databases and search engines.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-2a891514222c7fefbcc45259ee3bb8c2</data>
  <data key="d4">lightrag/evaluation/sample_documents/02_rag_architecture.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1775461447</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Embedding Model">
  <data key="d0">Embedding Model</data>
  <data key="d1">component</data>
  <data key="d2">The embedding model is the second component of the RAG system that converts text into vector representations for similarity search.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-2a891514222c7fefbcc45259ee3bb8c2</data>
  <data key="d4">lightrag/evaluation/sample_documents/02_rag_architecture.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1775461447</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Large Language Model">
  <data key="d0">Large Language Model</data>
  <data key="d1">component</data>
  <data key="d2">The large language model is the third component of the RAG system that generates responses based on retrieved context and synthesizes information from multiple sources.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-2a891514222c7fefbcc45259ee3bb8c2</data>
  <data key="d4">lightrag/evaluation/sample_documents/02_rag_architecture.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1775461447</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Vector Databases">
  <data key="d0">Vector Databases</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Vector databases are used within the retrieval system to store and manage large collections of vector representations for effective document retrieval.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-2a891514222c7fefbcc45259ee3bb8c2</data>
  <data key="d4">lightrag/evaluation/sample_documents/02_rag_architecture.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1775461447</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Search Engines">
  <data key="d0">Search Engines</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Search engines can function as retrieval systems in RAG architectures to find relevant documents from collections.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-2a891514222c7fefbcc45259ee3bb8c2</data>
  <data key="d4">lightrag/evaluation/sample_documents/02_rag_architecture.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1775461447</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Traditional RAG">
  <data key="d0">Traditional RAG</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Traditional RAG refers to older retrieval-augmented generation systems that are often more complex, slower, and limited in database integration compared to newer frameworks.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3ab88a7ea07b155c41c81dc1fa3ffb65</data>
  <data key="d4">lightrag/evaluation/sample_documents/03_lightrag_improvements.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1775461466</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Vector Database">
  <data key="d0">Vector Database</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Vector databases are storage systems optimized for handling vector representations of data, which are crucial for applications like retrieval-augmented generation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3ab88a7ea07b155c41c81dc1fa3ffb65</data>
  <data key="d4">lightrag/evaluation/sample_documents/03_lightrag_improvements.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1775461466</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="API Design">
  <data key="d0">API Design</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">API Design refers to the structure and functionality of application programming interfaces, which in the context of LightRAG, is designed to be simpler and more intuitive for developers to use compared to traditional systems.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3ab88a7ea07b155c41c81dc1fa3ffb65</data>
  <data key="d4">lightrag/evaluation/sample_documents/03_lightrag_improvements.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1775461466</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Retrieval Performance">
  <data key="d0">Retrieval Performance</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Retrieval Performance measures how quickly and efficiently a system can retrieve data, with LightRAG showing improvements in speed compared to traditional RAG approaches.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3ab88a7ea07b155c41c81dc1fa3ffb65</data>
  <data key="d4">lightrag/evaluation/sample_documents/03_lightrag_improvements.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1775461466</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Prompting Strategies">
  <data key="d0">Prompting Strategies</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Prompting Strategies are techniques used to structure queries or prompts in order to optimize the responses from a system, with LightRAG implementing refined strategies for better accuracy.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3ab88a7ea07b155c41c81dc1fa3ffb65</data>
  <data key="d4">lightrag/evaluation/sample_documents/03_lightrag_improvements.md</data>
